  "text": "Phagocytosis is the process by which invading pathogens and dead cells are efficiently removed by phagocytic cells, primarily macrophages. Macrophage phagocytosis plays an important role in host defense [CITATION_1] . The phagocytic activities of OV/RAW264.7 and ON/RAW264.7 cells were measured using fluorescent microspheres after co-incubation for 2 h. Phagocytosis rates and phagocytosis index of OV/RAW264.7 and ON/RAW264.7 cells were quantified using fluorescence microscopy (Figs. 4A and 4B) and flow cytometry (Figs. 4C and 4D ). OV/RAW264.7 and ON/RAW264.7 cells efficiently phagocytize fluorescent microspheres. However, ON/RAW264.7 cells exhibited a significantly higher phagocytosis rate and phagocytosis index against xenogeneic target microspheres than OV/RAW264.7 cells.",
